SIMPLE: resistless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resistless
<hw>Re*sist"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having no power to
resist; making no opposition.</def> <mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Incapable of being resisted; irresistible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Masters' commands come with a power <qex>resistless</qex>⟦br⟧
To such as owe them absolute subjection.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*sist"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*sist"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resoluble</ent>⟦br⟧
